Spain competed at the 1988 Summer Olympics in Seoul, Korea. 229 competitors, 200 men and 29 women, took part in 130 events in 24 sports.[1] No member of the Spanish archery delegation advanced past the preliminary round. Women's Individual Competition: Men's Individual Competition: Men's Team Competition: Men's 10.000 metres Men's Marathon Men's Long Jump Men's Decathlon Men's 20km Walk Men's 50km Walk Women's 4x400m Relay Women's 10.000 metres Men's Light Flyweight ( 48kg) Men's Flyweight ( 51kg)  Eight fencers, all men, represented Spain in 1988. Men's Individual Competition: Men's Team Competition: Men's 200m Freestyle Men's 400m Freestyle Men's 100m Backstroke Men's 200m Backstroke Men's 100m Breaststroke Men's 200m Breaststroke Men's 100m Butterfly Men's 200m Butterfly Men's 200m Individual Medley Men's 200m Individual Medley Men's 4x100m Medley Relay Women's 200m Breaststroke Women's 100m Butterfly Women's 200m Individual Medley Women's 4x100m Medley Relay Men's Singles Competition Men's Doubles Competition
